cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a method for neural network size minimization and supervised feature selection, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also includes experiments on image classification, which suggests a possible fit for cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the method involves stochastic filtering, which could be related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
